Brunei's Sultan Hassanal Bolkiah on Sunday extended a decade's long moratorium on the death penalty to a set of laws that set off a global outcry last month. In a televised speech, the sultan said Allah (God) would never hand down laws meant to inflict cruelty on others. Brunei gay man speaks out against anti-LGBT laws Brunei's new Islamic sharia laws may "encourage" people to dislike the LGBT community even more, a Brunei gay national told Reuters.